Arrange paper towel in a warm, breeze-free spot in the kitchen or some other convenient place in your house. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/8f\/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/8f\/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Place the flowers across the paper towel (use as many pieces as needed) and avoid overlapping any flowers (keep them all separate). {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7c\/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7c\/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Leave them to dry. They should dry within a day or two.

Before storing, ensure that the flowers are completely dry. Any moisture in them still will cause the growth of mildew and they'll have to be discarded. Store the flowers in an airtight container and keep them away from light. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
