Store in a cool and dry location. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Dry-Edible-Flowers-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
